@node "prefz" "Please read!"
                         IMPORTANT NOTICES TO READ
                         =========================

1. Since  Mail2YAM is free (I don't want money  from  you), I need a little
help  from  you  all:   please if you've problems, before write me, be sure
that you've read the documentation;

2. When you write me please tell me WHAT version of Mail2YAM you're using.

That's all.
@endnode

@node "fortune" "Random Fortune cookies"
                          Random fortune cookies
                          ======================

Mail2YAM supports random fortune coockies.
A  random fortune coockie is a random (really?) phrase to put at the end of
your mail.

                            @{b}*** IMPORTANT!!! ***@{ub}

There is a little limitation...  each phrase MUST BE one line length.
See "S/Fortune.txt" in this archive to see random fortune cookies format.

However, note that this feature is @{i}optional@{ui}.
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Mail2Yam Usage"
                            How to Use Mail2YAM
                            ===================

Usage: Mail2YAM <prefs|check|mailto> [<pophost> <username> <password>]

@{b}prefs@{ub}       Invokes mail2yam prefs-editor.

Important:   every  time  you launch prefs-editor and you abort the script,
the preference file (S:mail2yam.prefs) will be overwritten, then truncated.
You have to launch prefs-editor again and define all parameters to generate
FULL  AND  VALID  preference  file.  To see how it works, open a newcli and
enter:

mail2yam prefs

@{b}check@{ub}       Invokes mail2yam check mail.

NOTE: you need to be connected and TCP: device must be already mounted.

Mail2YAM  look in your mailbox if you've new messages.  If you've mail, M2Y
reports  you  how  messages  are  in your mailbox, so you can launch YAM to
retrieve  your  mail; else M2Y simply advise that you have no new mail.

To do this, you need to fill pophost, username and password keywords.
Here is an example:

mail2yam check server.mailbox.com alexursi pass-word

That means that mail2yam try to connect your mailserver @{b}server.mailbox.com@{ub},
sends your user id @{b}alexursi@{ub}, your password @{b}pass-word@{ub}, then
check in your mailbox for new mails.

@{b}mailto@{ub}      Invokes mail2yam mailto sequence.

Mail2YAM starts mailto procedure.
To do this, you need to fill destination address.
Example:

mail2yam mailto alexursi@luda.livorno.it

That  means  that  mail2yam starts mailto procedure, destination address is
mail2yam author ;-)

I suggest you to try my script locally...  it's the best way to know how it
works.
@endnode

@node "Introduction" "What is Mail2YAM?"
                             What is Mail2YAM?
                             =================

Mail2Yam  is  the  only  and  the one mailto script replacement for ANY WWW
browser.   This program has been tested on different machines (A1200, A2000
and  A4000)  and  reports  @{b}NO problems@{ub}.

BUT  if  you  find  a  bug,  please write me:  I will do my best to fix the
problem.
@endnode

