@node "install" "How Install Mail2YAM"
                           How Install Mail2Yam
                           ====================

1. Simply copy from this archive "c/mail2yam" to your c: directory.
   Then open a newcli and enter:

   C:Mail2YAM prefs

   And reply to each answer.

2. If you want to install mail2yam on...

                           @{b}Voyager@{ub}, click @{"here" link "Voyager Installation" 0}.
                           @{b}AWeb@{ub}   , click @{"here" link "AWeb Installation" 0}.
                          @{b}Ibrowse@{ub}ą, click @{"here" link "IBrowse Installation" 0}.


@{i}FOOTNOTES@{ui}

ą Tested only on Ibrowse 1.02 Commercial.
@endnode

@node "Voyager Installation" "... on Voyager"
                           VOYAGER Installation
                           ====================

Load  Voyager and go in prefs menu.  Then select "network", select "other",
then, on "mailto app", enter the following string:

                           c:mail2yam MAILTO %h

Use  this settings and exit.  Next time you load Voyager, when you click on
a "mailto:" reference, Voyager will launch Mail2YAM. Great!!!
@endnode

@node "AWeb Installation" "...on AWeb"
                             AWeb Installation
                             =================

Load AWeb and go on "Settings" menu', then select "Change Settings...".
Click  on  the  top  button  until  the button name will become...

                      "Network 3: External programs"

Ok, on the "Command" string gadget, enter:

                                c:mail2yam

Then, on "Argument" string gadget, enter simply...

                                 MAILTO %s

Click on Save button. @{b}You are done@{ub} :-)
@endnode

@node "IBrowse Installation" "... on Ibrowse"
                           IBrowse Installation
                           ====================

Load  Ibrowse  and  go  on "Preferences" menu', then select "Network" item.
Select   "E-Mail&Telnet"  (last  entry).   Now  select,  on  "Mailto"  box,
"External", then type on gadstring the following line:

                           c:mail2yam MAILTO %h

Then,  on Sendmail box, select `External' and leave an empty string. Click
on OK, then save settings.
@endnode

